  <div id="T1"> 
   <div class="table-caption">
    <span class="table-number">Figure 1.</span><span class="table-title">Template for each decision in the Important Decision Doc</span>
   </div> 
   <table frame="hsides" rules="rows">
    <thead valign="bottom">
     <tr>
      <th align="left" colspan="2"><p>23. <span style="font-family:sans-serif;font-size:1.5em;">☑</span> Declarative version of the final decision</p> </th>
     </tr>
    </thead>
    <tbody>
     <tr> 
      <td align="left" valign="top"><p><b>Question</b></p> </td> 
      <td align="left" valign="top"><p>This section introduces the question that requires a decision, and sets the stage, provides whatever context is necessary to understand the decision, etc.</p> </td>
     </tr>
     <tr> 
      <td align="left" valign="top"><p><b>Options</b></p> </td> 
      <td align="left" valign="top"> <p>• <b>Succinct option, with enough context and description</b></p> <p>   ○ Blah blah clarification</p> <p>   ○ Blah blah personal interpretation or example</p> <p>• <strike>More options, this one is rejected</strike></p> <p>   ○ <strike>Blah blah clarification</strike></p> <p>• <strike>More options, this one is rejected</strike></p> <br /> <p>Instructions:</p> <p>After the decision is made, <b>bold</b> the selected option, <strike>strike-out</strike> the others.</p> <p>• Rationale: Months from now, we’ll want to be able to skim the doc and understand the decisions. Currently, one has to parse the “Decision” paragraphs to figure out the final decision. Worst case, someone sees the options and guesses the wrong one was selected.</p> <p>• If the final decision is unlike the options listed, add that as a new option!</p> <p>• Move the selected option to the top of the list (and bold it).</p> <p>• Delete these instructions.</p> <br /> <p>Under each option, there should be sub-bullets with clarifying examples.</p> <p>• Rationale: It is common that months later we discover two people thought they were in agreement when they weren’t. Examples should be used to clarify edge cases.</p> </td>
     </tr>
     <tr> 
      <td align="left" valign="top"><p><b>Rationale</b></p> </td> 
      <td align="left" valign="top"><p>Confirm the chosen option language of the decision.</p> <br /> <p>Provide descriptive rationale confirming why <i>this</i> choice is the one we are going with, and explicitly address other options individually to speak to why those decisions were not chosen</p> </td>
     </tr>
     <tr> 
      <td align="left" valign="top"><p><b>Notes</b></p> </td> 
      <td align="left" valign="top"><p>Add any additional context or information needed</p> </td>
     </tr>
    </tbody>
   </table> 
  </div> 
