  <div id="UT1"> 
   <div class="table-caption">
    <span class="table-number">Figure 2.</span><span class="table-title">Examples of Important Decisions in Practice</span>
   </div> 
   <table frame="hsides" rules="rows">
    <thead valign="bottom">
     <tr>
      <th align="left" valign="top" colspan="2">1. <span style="font-family:sans-serif;font-size:1.5em;">☑</span> IdProvider will remain as-is in Azure</th>
     </tr>
    </thead>
    <tbody>
     <tr> 
      <td align="left" valign="top"><p><b>Question</b></p> </td> 
      <td align="left" valign="top">What’s our strategy for migrating IdProvider?</td>
     </tr>
     <tr> 
      <td align="left" valign="top"><p><b>Options</b></p> </td> 
      <td align="left" valign="top"><p>• <b>Leave as is in Azure.</b></p> <p>• <strike>Move to GCP.</strike></p> <p>• <strike>Run a separate instance in GCP for public logins, separate from Teams.</strike></p> </td>
     </tr>
     <tr> 
      <td align="left" valign="top"><p><b>Rationale</b></p> </td> 
      <td align="left" valign="top"><p>No need to move this, given it’s already working as is and we do not want to add additional scope.</p> </td>
     </tr>
     <tr> 
      <td align="left" valign="top"><p><b>Notes</b></p> </td> 
      <td align="left" valign="top"><p>IdProvider is a service that provides email/password credentials for our Q&amp;A sites and Talent. It was moved from the DC to Azure in 2023.</p> </td>
     </tr>
